SIMPLE: harpsichord
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Harpsichord
<hw>Harp"si*chord</hw> <pr>(-k⟦ocir⟧rd)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>harpechorde</ets>, in which the <ets>harpe</ets> is of German
origin. See <er>Harp</er>, and <er>Chord</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Mus.)</fld>
<def>A harp-shaped instrument of music set horizontally on legs, like
the grand piano, with strings of wire, played by the fingers, by means
of keys provided with quills, instead of hammers, for striking the
strings. It is now superseded by the piano.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>harpsichordist</ent>⟦br⟧
